2
00:00:17.880 --> 00:00:22.010
Setting out before the day breaks

3
00:00:18.390 --> 00:00:22.120
Yoru ga akeru mae ni tabidatou

4
00:00:21.720 --> 00:00:26.520
To greet an unknown tomorrow

5
00:00:22.240 --> 00:00:26.490
Mada minu ashita wo mukae ni ikou

6
00:00:26.270 --> 00:00:30.100
We have no regrets in our resolve

7
00:00:26.790 --> 00:00:30.290
Sou kimeta koto kui wa nai

8
00:00:29.900 --> 00:00:33.190
(Oh, I know what I’m supposed to do)

9
00:00:32.860 --> 00:00:36.860
No matter what kind of trials lie ahead,

10
00:00:33.360 --> 00:00:36.980
Donna shiren ga machiukete iyouto

11
00:00:36.530 --> 00:00:41.460
Nothing can stop my throbbing heart

12
00:00:37.030 --> 00:00:41.490
Takanaru kodou tomerare wa shinai

13
00:00:41.070 --> 00:00:46.160
There is only one place to go

14
00:00:41.590 --> 00:00:46.130
Mezasu basho wa tada hitotsu

15
00:00:45.870 --> 00:00:48.070
(Fly to the light)

16
00:00:47.620 --> 00:00:51.790
Bonds forged through battle

17
00:00:48.140 --> 00:00:51.770
Tatakai no hate ni eta kizuna

18
00:00:51.420 --> 00:00:55.500
I won’t let anyone get hurt

19
00:00:51.940 --> 00:00:55.540
Dare nimo kizutsukesase wa shinai

20
00:00:55.090 --> 00:00:58.300
When I open my clenched fist,

21
00:00:55.600 --> 00:00:58.370
Nigiri shimeta te hirakeba

22
00:00:57.880 --> 00:01:01.550
I will find power there

23
00:00:58.400 --> 00:01:01.610
Soko ni chikara ga yadoru

24
00:01:01.220 --> 00:01:03.930
So let’s start

25
00:01:01.710 --> 00:01:03.980
Saa hajimeyou

26
00:01:03.600 --> 00:01:09.100
The new world is calling

27
00:01:04.080 --> 00:01:09.110
Atarashii sekai ga yondeiru

28
00:01:08.680 --> 00:01:11.480
See now look

29
00:01:09.180 --> 00:01:11.580
Hora mite goran

30
00:01:11.060 --> 00:01:17.860
No matter how many seas separate us

31
00:01:11.580 --> 00:01:17.950
Ikutsu no umi hedatete itato shitemo

32
00:01:17.530 --> 00:01:21.610
I’ve always got your back

33
00:01:18.020 --> 00:01:21.590
Itsudatte sasaeteiru

34
00:01:21.110 --> 00:01:25.280
Don’t be afraid to advance

35
00:01:21.610 --> 00:01:25.580
Osorezu ni mae e

36
00:01:25.280 --> 00:01:27.650
Don’t forget

37
00:01:25.790 --> 00:01:27.650
Wasurenaide

38
00:01:27.200 --> 00:01:29.040
We fight together

39
00:01:29.160 --> 00:01:36.960
I’ve never spoiled the memory

40
00:01:29.650 --> 00:01:37.060
Kegashita koto wa nai

41
00:01:36.840 --> 00:01:39.670
Of the vast infinite sky,

42
00:01:37.360 --> 00:01:39.800
Ano hi miageta

43
00:01:39.300 --> 00:01:44.800
That I gazed upon that day

44
00:01:39.800 --> 00:01:44.800
Dokomademo takaku hiroi sora

45
00:01:44.340 --> 00:01:48.270
We’ve come a long way

46
00:01:44.830 --> 00:01:48.370
Zuibun to tooku made kita

47
00:01:47.970 --> 00:01:52.170
Each with our own pledges in our hearts

48
00:01:48.470 --> 00:01:52.170
Sorezore no chikai wo mune ni

49
00:01:51.730 --> 00:01:54.770
There is no doubt

50
00:01:52.240 --> 00:01:54.770
Mayoi nado nai

51
00:01:54.350 --> 00:01:59.230
There are burdens we must bear

52
00:01:54.840 --> 00:01:59.200
Seou mono ga aru

53
00:01:58.860 --> 00:02:01.740
The sun will rise

54
00:01:59.370 --> 00:02:01.710
Hi ga nobori

55
00:02:01.360 --> 00:02:06.660
And even illuminate our sorrows

56
00:02:01.860 --> 00:02:06.780
Kanashimi sae hitoshiku terasu

57
00:02:06.330 --> 00:02:09.080
Yes, I believe it!

58
00:02:06.810 --> 00:02:09.210
Shinjiterunda

59
00:02:08.790 --> 00:02:15.500
One Piece will someday bind us together

60
00:02:09.280 --> 00:02:15.640
Itsuka hitotsu ni tsunagaru mirai wo

61
00:02:15.130 --> 00:02:19.090
Let’s go and find it!

62
00:02:15.640 --> 00:02:19.320
Issho ni mitsuke ni ikou

63
00:02:18.840 --> 00:02:22.880
You’re irreplaceable

64
00:02:19.340 --> 00:02:23.510
Kimi no kawari wa inai

65
00:02:23.180 --> 00:02:25.050
Don’t forget

66
00:02:23.690 --> 00:02:25.350
Wasurenaide

67
00:02:24.930 --> 00:02:27.430
We fight together

68
00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:34.400
Calm Belt

69
00:02:43.240 --> 00:02:46.090
Look! It's a huge sea king!

70
00:02:46.090 --> 00:02:48.010
And it's... fighting something?!

71
00:02:57.100 --> 00:02:59.690
It's dead! Something out there killed it!

72
00:02:59.830 --> 00:03:05.460
Cheer

73
00:03:00.600 --> 00:03:02.000
But it's huge!

74
00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:03.800
I couldn't see what did it!

75
00:03:03.800 --> 00:03:05.500
This sea is scary!

76
00:03:09.230 --> 00:03:10.270
– Huh?!
– Huh?!

77
00:03:10.270 --> 00:03:11.440
A guy...?!

78
00:03:11.440 --> 00:03:13.610
Hey! Who are you?!

79
00:03:16.340 --> 00:03:17.640
What a pain...

80
00:03:18.610 --> 00:03:19.580
D...

81
00:03:21.350 --> 00:03:21.920
Okay!

82
00:03:21.920 --> 00:03:22.810
D...!

83
00:03:22.810 --> 00:03:24.790
Dark King Rayleigh!

84
00:03:24.790 --> 00:03:26.390
– What?!
– What?!

85
00:03:26.390 --> 00:03:30.100
Oh, it's you guys. We met
at Sabaody Archipelago.

86
00:03:35.000 --> 00:03:38.290
He was the first mate of Roger,
the King of the Pirates!

87
00:03:38.290 --> 00:03:44.600
Well, my ship sunk during a storm,
so I had to swim the rest of the way.

88
00:03:44.600 --> 00:03:49.600
A storm?! This is the Calm Belt;
these waters are never rough!

89
00:03:49.600 --> 00:03:50.780
What storm?!

90
00:03:50.780 --> 00:03:55.850
Wait...! So your ship wrecked farther away,
meaning you swam that entire distance?!

91
00:03:56.800 --> 00:03:58.690
I have a good breaststroke.

92
00:03:58.690 --> 00:04:01.050
That's not the point!

93
00:04:01.050 --> 00:04:03.680
Then, the one fighting that sea king...

94
00:04:03.680 --> 00:04:05.240
– ...was you?!
– ...was you?!

95
00:04:05.240 --> 00:04:09.020
Only a legendary pirate could do that!

96
00:04:10.700 --> 00:04:12.160
Oh, I'm sorry.

97
00:04:12.160 --> 00:04:14.670
– What are you sorry for?!
– What are you sorry for?!

98
00:04:14.670 --> 00:04:16.570
Oh, right!

99
00:04:18.500 --> 00:04:21.970
I assume Luffy is here on this island.

100
00:04:26.700 --> 00:04:28.590
Did you hear?

101
00:04:28.180 --> 00:04:32.820
Center of the Island
 Isle of Women, Amazon Lily

102
00:04:28.590 --> 00:04:32.820
The Snake Princess and her entourage
just left to deliver food to Luffy!

103
00:04:32.820 --> 00:04:35.640
I wanna stretch his body again!

104
00:04:35.640 --> 00:04:39.390
They said they'll invite him over
when he gets better.

105
00:04:39.390 --> 00:04:41.450
I can't wait!

106
00:04:41.450 --> 00:04:44.360
I didn't expect to see him again this soon!

107
00:04:45.590 --> 00:04:48.970
Yeah, maybe I'll make clothes for him again...

108
00:04:48.970 --> 00:04:49.970
without frills!

109
00:04:55.350 --> 00:04:59.200
Oh, to be separated from my dearest
so soon after our marriage...

110
00:04:59.200 --> 00:05:01.910
I feel like a tragic heroine!

111
00:05:01.910 --> 00:05:06.290
"But Hancock... No, my dear wife!"

112
00:05:06.290 --> 00:05:07.670
"Y-Yes!"

113
00:05:07.670 --> 00:05:09.350
"No matter how far apart we are,

114
00:05:09.350 --> 00:05:11.690
our love will endure forever!"

115
00:05:11.690 --> 00:05:14.060
"Luffy!"

116
00:05:14.060 --> 00:05:20.500
Oh, my sweet husband!
Right now, my heart is aflame!

117
00:05:20.500 --> 00:05:22.990
I keep telling you, Snake Princess,

118
00:05:22.990 --> 00:05:27.140
just because someone hugs you
and calls you by nyame,

119
00:05:27.140 --> 00:05:28.840
it doesn't mean you are married.

120
00:05:28.840 --> 00:05:31.780
Then, what constitutes marriage?

121
00:05:31.780 --> 00:05:34.950
Ah... There's nyo easy answer to this.

122
00:05:37.940 --> 00:05:41.220
You can't go to Sabaody with those wounds.

123
00:05:41.220 --> 00:05:45.100
But I gotta see my friends right away!

124
00:05:45.100 --> 00:05:48.690
I promised them I'd be there.

125
00:05:48.690 --> 00:05:50.420
But listen...

126
00:05:51.100 --> 00:05:53.970
Hm? It looks like...

127
00:05:53.970 --> 00:05:56.300
that submarine crew is gone.

128
00:05:56.300 --> 00:05:58.300
Oh, Luffy!

129
00:05:58.300 --> 00:06:00.910
What?! It's old Rayleigh!

130
00:06:01.750 --> 00:06:03.540
Glad I found you so quickly.

131
00:06:03.540 --> 00:06:05.890
What're you doing here?!

132
00:06:05.890 --> 00:06:10.520
I was about to go back to Sabaody
using your vivre card.

133
00:06:12.150 --> 00:06:13.390
Is everyone...?

134
00:06:13.390 --> 00:06:16.790
No, it's unlikely they've made it back yet.

135
00:06:17.350 --> 00:06:21.090
I gave my vivre card to Shakky...

136
00:06:21.090 --> 00:06:26.500
Otherwise... I couldn't move
about freely like this.

137
00:06:26.500 --> 00:06:31.900
Dark King Rayleigh!
Is it really you? I can't believe it!

138
00:06:31.900 --> 00:06:34.820
You must be the former Warlord...

139
00:06:34.820 --> 00:06:35.790
What's wrong?

140
00:06:35.790 --> 00:06:39.610
I just... I didn't expect
to meet a living legend here.

141
00:06:40.200 --> 00:06:43.100
Here. Isn't this hat important to you?

142
00:06:43.100 --> 00:06:44.620
It is. Thanks.

143
00:06:49.050 --> 00:06:53.630
After all... just doesn't feel right without it!

144
00:06:56.610 --> 00:06:59.700
Did you happen to see a pirate crew here?

145
00:06:59.700 --> 00:07:03.040
Trafalgar Law? His ship just left.

146
00:07:03.840 --> 00:07:07.640
He recommends another
two weeks of bed rest.

147
00:07:10.140 --> 00:07:12.340
He saved your life, didn't he?

148
00:07:17.650 --> 00:07:21.600
What a waste! After coming all this way...

149
00:07:21.600 --> 00:07:24.900
I never got to see the female-only empire...

150
00:07:24.900 --> 00:07:26.810
Bears were allowed in.

151
00:07:26.810 --> 00:07:28.130
– Shut up!
– Shut up!

152
00:07:28.130 --> 00:07:29.600
I'm sorry.

153
00:07:29.600 --> 00:07:31.190
– What a pushover!
– What a pushover!

154
00:07:31.200 --> 00:07:34.100
I wonder what the Dark King is up to.

155
00:07:34.100 --> 00:07:37.010
Storms tend to follow in the wake of a D.

156
00:07:38.300 --> 00:07:40.910
I can't wait to see him again...

157
00:07:41.700 --> 00:07:45.900
Is that Rayleigh?!
I cannyot believe my eyes!

158
00:07:45.900 --> 00:07:50.020
Oh, Gloriosa! It's been awhile!

159
00:07:50.020 --> 00:07:51.390
Rayleigh!

160
00:07:51.390 --> 00:07:52.490
Mr. Ray!

161
00:07:52.490 --> 00:07:54.860
Oh, you two are here too!

162
00:07:54.860 --> 00:07:56.300
Luffy!

163
00:07:56.300 --> 00:07:57.590
– Hey, Big Sis!
– Hey, Big Sis!

164
00:07:57.590 --> 00:08:00.560
– Don't ignore the man who saved your life!
– Don't ignore the man who saved your life!

165
00:08:00.560 --> 00:08:04.200
Then... you know old Rayleigh?

166
00:08:04.200 --> 00:08:05.640
We do.

167
00:08:05.640 --> 00:08:08.100
It's a long story.

168
00:08:08.100 --> 00:08:10.410
Luffy, it's good to see you up and about.

169
00:08:10.410 --> 00:08:12.100
I lost sleep from worry.

170
00:08:12.100 --> 00:08:15.700
You must be hungry. I brought some food.

171
00:08:15.700 --> 00:08:17.840
So go ahead and dig in...

172
00:08:17.840 --> 00:08:19.900
You cannyot even look at him.

173
00:08:19.900 --> 00:08:22.710
How can you claim to be married?

174
00:08:22.710 --> 00:08:23.800
Serve him a–

175
00:08:25.090 --> 00:08:27.330
Serve him a meal already!

176
00:08:30.120 --> 00:08:34.430
Jinbe! This food is not for you!

177
00:08:35.010 --> 00:08:36.410
You can only have a little.

178
00:08:36.410 --> 00:08:40.830
O-Okay. Luffy, why don't we just eat?

179
00:08:42.830 --> 00:08:48.440
Luffy, you have to eat. To eat is to live!

180
00:09:03.600 --> 00:09:06.830
That's it! That's the Luffy I know!

181
00:09:10.090 --> 00:09:13.130
Thank you for bringing me
the letter from Shakky.

182
00:09:14.630 --> 00:09:17.600
Sounds like she has nyot changed.

183
00:09:17.600 --> 00:09:21.890
Yeah, she hasn't changed a bit
since you were living in Sabaody.

184
00:09:21.890 --> 00:09:23.880
She's doing fine.

185
00:09:23.880 --> 00:09:30.800
These girls of yours have grown quite beautiful
and strong over the past thirteen years.

186
00:09:30.800 --> 00:09:34.090
Rayleigh, Shakky, and Elder Nyon,

187
00:09:34.090 --> 00:09:39.320
the three of you protected us when
we were running from the Celestial Dragons.

188
00:09:39.320 --> 00:09:41.790
But we have a problem.

189
00:09:41.790 --> 00:09:46.690
We're supposed to shelter
Luffy from the Marines.

190
00:09:46.690 --> 00:09:50.290
It's true that Rayleigh knyows
Luffy from before,

191
00:09:50.290 --> 00:09:56.110
but that he was able to guess Luffy's
location so easily is indeed troubling.

192
00:09:56.110 --> 00:09:58.910
Huh?! What a familiar face!

193
00:09:58.910 --> 00:10:01.610
You wouldn't happen to be
Rayleigh, would you?!

194
00:10:01.610 --> 00:10:04.460
You just nyoticed?!
Get your head out of the clouds!

195
00:10:06.000 --> 00:10:09.960
No, I don't think the Marines will
be able to guess his whereabouts.

196
00:10:10.690 --> 00:10:14.240
To begin with, the one who sent him here...

197
00:10:14.240 --> 00:10:17.890
told me the direction in which to look.

198
00:10:18.770 --> 00:10:21.700
I'm an officer in the Revolutionary Army.

199
00:10:21.700 --> 00:10:23.470
We're connected by fate.

200
00:10:23.470 --> 00:10:25.880
I wish to help them escape.

201
00:10:26.110 --> 00:10:28.910
Oh? I'm in disbelief.

202
00:10:29.790 --> 00:10:32.580
So where's our little Monkey now?

203
00:10:33.500 --> 00:10:35.280
Beats me...

204
00:10:38.300 --> 00:10:41.220
Let me apologize for my abrupt manner earlier.

205
00:10:41.860 --> 00:10:44.300
Can I talk to you for a moment?

206
00:10:45.090 --> 00:10:46.720
I don't have...

207
00:10:47.810 --> 00:10:49.390
much time left.

208
00:10:50.730 --> 00:10:52.400
Straw Hat should be...

209
00:10:53.700 --> 00:10:58.100
If you follow the direction
Bartholomew Kuma launched Luffy,

210
00:10:58.100 --> 00:11:01.010
you find the Isle of Women.

211
00:11:01.010 --> 00:11:06.440
When I thought about how Luffy
managed to infiltrate the great prison...

212
00:11:06.920 --> 00:11:13.150
it dawned on me that Hancock must've
smuggled him aboard a Marine ship.

213
00:11:16.990 --> 00:11:20.630
Since Hancock hates both
the government and men,

214
00:11:20.630 --> 00:11:25.640
it's unlikely she'd board a government ship,
especially not to shelter a man.

215
00:11:26.700 --> 00:11:29.000
This is all just speculation, though.

216
00:11:29.770 --> 00:11:31.700
Then how about this?

217
00:11:33.390 --> 00:11:38.100
Let's suppose Hancock fell
in love with our little Monkey.

218
00:11:38.100 --> 00:11:39.980
Then everything makes sense.

219
00:11:42.110 --> 00:11:44.950
Our little Monkey is a real stud.

220
00:11:46.320 --> 00:11:49.410
And if I were Hancock,

221
00:11:49.410 --> 00:11:53.890
I'd pull one over on the Marines
by hiding him on the Isle of Women.

222
00:11:55.210 --> 00:11:58.030
The idea seems pretty subjective, Shakky.

223
00:12:01.010 --> 00:12:04.600
A woman's intuition is a fearsome thing.

224
00:12:04.600 --> 00:12:06.270
That's my Shakky!

225
00:12:06.270 --> 00:12:09.810
She could nyot be more right!
See for yourself.

226
00:12:09.810 --> 00:12:12.940
Oh? You like it? Good!

227
00:12:13.900 --> 00:12:17.860
The Marines would never act
on such a ridiculous theory.

228
00:12:18.600 --> 00:12:20.590
So this place is safe.

229
00:12:21.200 --> 00:12:23.690
Now, let's get down to business.

230
00:12:24.990 --> 00:12:25.990
Luffy.

231
00:12:27.160 --> 00:12:32.650
You said you're gonna head
for Sabaody, didn't you?

232
00:12:35.200 --> 00:12:37.440
I gotta get back to my crew.

233
00:12:39.400 --> 00:12:42.910
And you're sure you want to do that?

234
00:12:45.810 --> 00:12:47.750
Sabaody Archipelago...

235
00:12:49.100 --> 00:12:52.150
Don't you remember what happened there?

236
00:13:00.330 --> 00:13:04.460
Everyone, focus on escaping!

237
00:13:04.460 --> 00:13:10.170
We can't beat these guys!
Not now! Not yet!

238
00:13:13.200 --> 00:13:18.340
I couldn't save even one of my friends...!

239
00:13:29.720 --> 00:13:35.310
Do you think you can face those
tremendous powers as you are now?

240
00:13:52.140 --> 00:13:53.850
But... I...

241
00:13:53.850 --> 00:13:58.400
Do you want to be reunited with your
friends just to endure the same fate?

242
00:13:59.850 --> 00:14:02.950
I have a suggestion.

243
00:14:03.750 --> 00:14:05.890
Of course, whether you follow it...

244
00:14:07.000 --> 00:14:08.060
is up to you!

245
00:14:16.600 --> 00:14:22.210
Meanwhile, on the Bowin
Archipelago in the Grand Line...
Bowin Archipelago
Grand Line

246
00:14:22.940 --> 00:14:25.910
Stop! Usopp'n!

247
00:14:25.910 --> 00:14:28.330
Don't stop me, Heracles'n!

248
00:14:28.330 --> 00:14:30.720
Usopp is...

249
00:14:30.720 --> 00:14:33.890
moving his body,
which has grown immensely...

250
00:14:33.890 --> 00:14:36.490
from eating the forest's
abundant variety of food...

251
00:14:39.830 --> 00:14:41.600
and is running.

252
00:14:43.100 --> 00:14:45.030
It's impossible'n!

253
00:14:45.030 --> 00:14:47.200
No, it's not! I just have to keep trying!

254
00:14:47.820 --> 00:14:49.330
I can do it this time!

255
00:14:54.330 --> 00:14:55.410
There you are!

256
00:14:59.540 --> 00:15:02.210
Get out of my way!

257
00:15:02.990 --> 00:15:04.920
Lethal...

258
00:15:07.280 --> 00:15:10.250
Yikes'n! Usopp'n!

259
00:15:15.500 --> 00:15:17.890
Are you okay'n, Usopp'n?

260
00:15:18.780 --> 00:15:20.090
Damn...

261
00:15:20.090 --> 00:15:22.270
You're too reckless'n.

262
00:15:22.270 --> 00:15:24.370
If you try to get off of this island,

263
00:15:25.040 --> 00:15:27.810
terrifying creatures will halt your progress...

264
00:15:27.810 --> 00:15:31.040
and push you back into the forest'n!

265
00:15:37.390 --> 00:15:41.690
Nothing will stop you from
entering the island'n...

266
00:15:42.600 --> 00:15:45.200
but once you've set foot on it, you're dead!

267
00:15:45.200 --> 00:15:47.430
No one leaves this island alive'n!

268
00:15:47.430 --> 00:15:49.440
And my name is...

269
00:15:49.440 --> 00:15:51.300
Heracles'n!

270
00:15:52.410 --> 00:15:55.760
What?! Usopp'n! Where'd you go?!

271
00:16:01.670 --> 00:16:03.110
Oh! Danger's afoot'n!

272
00:16:03.110 --> 00:16:06.050
A great sea beast has come to the island'n!

273
00:16:06.050 --> 00:16:09.280
Usopp'n is in danger!

274
00:16:12.500 --> 00:16:17.210
The sweet scent wafting
from the Bowin Archipelago...

275
00:16:17.210 --> 00:16:19.930
draws in giant insects and massive birds...

276
00:16:19.930 --> 00:16:23.310
and even terrible monsters and sea kings.

277
00:16:24.890 --> 00:16:25.860
A sea hippo!

278
00:16:28.410 --> 00:16:31.500
No time to stand here gawking at it...!

279
00:16:31.500 --> 00:16:35.350
The scents lure them deeper into the island,

280
00:16:35.350 --> 00:16:38.940
where they find that
the forest is filled with food.

281
00:16:42.690 --> 00:16:44.960
Entering the island is one thing...

282
00:16:46.780 --> 00:16:48.830
but leaving proves difficult!

283
00:16:52.890 --> 00:16:53.960
Outta my way!

284
00:16:53.960 --> 00:16:56.900
Lethal Exploding Star!

285
00:16:58.600 --> 00:17:00.870
I'm getting off this island!

286
00:17:00.870 --> 00:17:05.100
Stop getting in my way!

287
00:17:05.700 --> 00:17:07.130
Usopp'n!

288
00:17:08.770 --> 00:17:10.810
The island is about to move again!

289
00:17:10.810 --> 00:17:12.310
What?

290
00:17:16.150 --> 00:17:19.390
Usopp'n! Hang onto a tree!

291
00:17:19.390 --> 00:17:20.820
This again?!

292
00:17:20.820 --> 00:17:23.570
It's preparing to feed!

293
00:17:29.700 --> 00:17:33.360
This flower that's disguised as an island is called...

294
00:17:45.910 --> 00:17:51.680
the Bowin Archipelago, a carnivorous plant also
known by its scientific name, the stomach baron!

295
00:17:53.210 --> 00:17:55.950
Usopp'n!

296
00:18:04.600 --> 00:18:06.500
What's the matter with you, Usopp'n?!

297
00:18:08.970 --> 00:18:13.570
Ever since that news coo brought the paper,
your whole demeanor has changed!

298
00:18:17.010 --> 00:18:18.580
I...

299
00:18:19.040 --> 00:18:26.180
I don't have a single moment to waste here!

300
00:18:29.620 --> 00:18:35.430
Luffy lost his brother in the war...!

301
00:18:35.430 --> 00:18:41.030
I'm sure he's going through hell right now!

302
00:18:58.410 --> 00:19:02.320
When your friend is having a hard time...

303
00:19:02.320 --> 00:19:07.310
you should be there for him!

304
00:19:08.230 --> 00:19:12.260
Luffy!

305
00:19:14.330 --> 00:19:18.070
Birdie Kingdom

306
00:19:18.070 --> 00:19:22.650
You go now, little tanuki?
We just become friends!

307
00:19:23.910 --> 00:19:29.600
I am. I read in the newspaper
that my friend is in trouble,

308
00:19:29.600 --> 00:19:32.110
so I need to hurry and get back.

309
00:19:33.010 --> 00:19:35.490
I met Luffy's brother in Alabasta.

310
00:19:36.200 --> 00:19:38.820
How could such a terrible thing happen?

311
00:19:39.550 --> 00:19:43.710
I need to hurry back to Luffy
and treat his wounds.

312
00:19:43.710 --> 00:19:45.600
He can't help but act recklessly.

313
00:19:46.390 --> 00:19:47.750
Little tanuki...

314
00:19:47.750 --> 00:19:51.800
I'm glad you were able to
make peace with the birds.

315
00:19:51.800 --> 00:19:56.170
It all thanks to little tanuki
risking life to persuade birds!

316
00:19:56.170 --> 00:19:57.480
Well, y'know...

317
00:19:57.480 --> 00:20:01.510
You guys, try to be nice
to the humans, okay?!

318
00:20:02.310 --> 00:20:08.020
The humans only need the plants
that grow on the tree.

319
00:20:08.020 --> 00:20:09.300
He right!

320
00:20:09.300 --> 00:20:13.040
We not hunt egg. We not harm you.

321
00:20:13.040 --> 00:20:18.020
We not same as people
who force you from homeland!

322
00:20:18.930 --> 00:20:25.200
I have to say, the medicine harvested from
the plants on this tree work very quickly.

323
00:20:25.200 --> 00:20:26.920
My wounds are about healed.

324
00:20:26.920 --> 00:20:32.140
Yeah! They very special
recipes from ancestors.

325
00:20:33.600 --> 00:20:38.890
If I had to choose, I'd prefer to stay
on this island and research its flora.

326
00:20:38.890 --> 00:20:42.300
I'm sure I've never come across
their components before.

327
00:20:42.300 --> 00:20:43.900
But there's no time...!

328
00:20:43.900 --> 00:20:45.460
Come other time!

329
00:20:45.460 --> 00:20:48.590
He right! We give little tanuki big welcome!

330
00:20:48.590 --> 00:20:50.730
– Yeah! Yeah!
– Yeah! Yeah!

331
00:20:50.730 --> 00:20:53.660
Really? You'd do that for me?

332
00:20:55.080 --> 00:20:59.940
After I reunite with my friends,
I'll definitely tell them about this place!

333
00:20:59.940 --> 00:21:03.510
And then I'll come see you all again!

334
00:21:04.680 --> 00:21:07.740
Here. You get hungry on long trip.

335
00:21:07.740 --> 00:21:09.240
Thanks.

336
00:21:09.240 --> 00:21:11.330
Come again, little tanuki!

337
00:21:13.460 --> 00:21:15.960
It's cotton candy!

338
00:21:15.960 --> 00:21:19.470
Okay, everyone! Try and get along!

339
00:21:20.630 --> 00:21:23.490
– Bye-bye, little tanuki!
– Bye-bye, little tanuki!

340
00:21:23.490 --> 00:21:26.790
All right, I've got my lunch
and my cotton candy.

341
00:21:26.790 --> 00:21:29.950
I'm all set to meet back up
with Luffy and the rest!

342
00:21:30.870 --> 00:21:33.100
I don't have a pirate ship!

343
00:21:33.880 --> 00:21:36.040
Ah! See you!

344
00:21:36.040 --> 00:21:39.500
Whoa, we're flying so high and fast!

345
00:21:39.500 --> 00:21:42.050
I'll catch up to the others in no time!

346
00:21:43.900 --> 00:21:47.360
Hey, news coo! Can I have a newspaper?

347
00:21:48.600 --> 00:21:51.780
I'll just read while I enjoy my meal.

348
00:21:51.780 --> 00:21:55.690
All the details of the war
should be coming to light now.

349
00:21:59.770 --> 00:22:02.100
What?! No way!

350
00:22:03.470 --> 00:22:06.200
Why?! What's going on here?!

351
00:22:06.200 --> 00:22:08.680
What made Luffy do this...?!

352
00:22:11.490 --> 00:22:14.600
This is Gloom Island on the Grand Line:

353
00:22:11.740 --> 00:22:17.150
Gloom Island

354
00:22:14.600 --> 00:22:17.400
the remnants of the Muggy Kingdom.

355
00:22:17.400 --> 00:22:20.670
An old castle stands resolute
against this decrepit land.

356
00:22:20.670 --> 00:22:26.160
But a few years ago, a certain man
took up residence there.

357
00:22:26.160 --> 00:22:29.490
How could Master Moria die in the war?!

358
00:22:39.590 --> 00:22:43.140
This is torture for my ears.
Take your wailing outside.

359
00:22:43.140 --> 00:22:47.470
How coldhearted of you! Is that any way
to talk to a person in mourning?!

360
00:22:47.470 --> 00:22:52.020
Is it too much to offer a few kind words
and to bring me a cup of hot cocoa?

361
00:22:52.020 --> 00:22:54.360
Don't forget, I'm your guest!

362
00:22:54.360 --> 00:22:55.890
An uninvited guest.

363
00:22:55.890 --> 00:22:59.680
You're squatters who took
advantage of my absence.

364
00:22:59.680 --> 00:23:00.730
Regardless...

365
00:23:01.790 --> 00:23:03.890
this article lacks credibility.

366
00:23:03.890 --> 00:23:08.800
What?! Then Master Moria possibly
survived the war?! Are you for real?!

367
00:23:08.800 --> 00:23:12.090
I am not certain whether he still lives...

368
00:23:12.090 --> 00:23:14.910
but if memory serves,

369
00:23:14.910 --> 00:23:19.490
Moria was still alive when I last
saw him on the battlefield.

370
00:23:19.490 --> 00:23:23.780
But if he didn't die in battle,
why run such an article?!

371
00:23:27.490 --> 00:23:28.620
Oni...

372
00:23:29.830 --> 00:23:31.020
Giri!

373
00:23:39.590 --> 00:23:41.490
Saliva won't heal that!

374
00:23:41.490 --> 00:23:43.800
Where did you pick up that folk remedy?!

375
00:23:48.190 --> 00:23:51.810
Damn these guys... How long till
they stop showing me up?!

376
00:23:52.400 --> 00:23:55.580
I'll never make it to the sea at this rate!

377
00:24:04.590 --> 00:24:05.940
Hawk Eye...

378
00:24:07.000 --> 00:24:09.390
You departed the castle some time ago,

379
00:24:09.390 --> 00:24:12.460
and yet you remain, Roronoa?

380
00:24:12.460 --> 00:24:17.300
It seems the rowboat I lent you
has been rendered useless.

381
00:24:17.300 --> 00:24:19.100
Put a sock in it!

382
00:24:19.100 --> 00:24:23.640
I can use it like a piece of driftwood
if I swim while holding onto it!

383
00:24:24.110 --> 00:24:28.340
This loyalty to your crew is touching,
but do not underestimate these beasts.

384
00:24:29.160 --> 00:24:33.990
Known as humandrills, they are cunning
baboons who develop by imitating humans.

385
00:24:33.990 --> 00:24:35.990
Humandrills?

386
00:24:35.990 --> 00:24:40.790
Were they to dwell among peaceful humans,
they, too, would be peaceful.

387
00:24:40.790 --> 00:24:42.890
But this land...

388
00:24:43.900 --> 00:24:48.110
was ravaged by a brutal war seven years ago.

389
00:24:49.000 --> 00:24:54.400
When I made this island my home,
the scent of blood and smoke yet lingered.

390
00:24:54.400 --> 00:24:57.250
The sea of corpses made it
nigh impossible to walk.

391
00:24:58.010 --> 00:25:03.300
To make my point, these beasts spent their
formative years watching ferocious humans.

392
00:25:03.300 --> 00:25:05.580
Their proficiency with human weaponry...

393
00:25:05.580 --> 00:25:08.260
transformed them into warriors of the forest.

394
00:25:08.790 --> 00:25:12.230
Mankind rules over the animals
with weapons and intelligence.

395
00:25:12.920 --> 00:25:15.850
But an animal with a weapon
is frighteningly strong.

396
00:25:16.710 --> 00:25:20.390
Fitting opponents, perhaps, for a cocksure youth.

397
00:25:20.390 --> 00:25:21.900
You mean me?!

398
00:25:21.900 --> 00:25:24.300
Who else would I mean?

399
00:25:24.300 --> 00:25:26.800
It's dreadfully late. Come to my castle.

400
00:25:26.800 --> 00:25:29.340
The beasts dare not venture near my abode.

401
00:25:30.400 --> 00:25:33.690
I don't take orders from you!

402
00:25:33.690 --> 00:25:35.980
I'm going out to sea, right now!

403
00:25:36.800 --> 00:25:38.040
So be it.

404
00:25:39.300 --> 00:25:40.380
Do what you will.

405
00:25:43.010 --> 00:25:45.890
I don't give a damn about
any warriors of the forest...

406
00:25:45.890 --> 00:25:49.150
I can't spend another moment around here!

407
00:25:58.200 --> 00:26:00.080
Meanwhile...

408
00:26:00.080 --> 00:26:05.280
in a country that researches weather,
the small sky island Weatheria...

409
00:26:10.400 --> 00:26:14.290
Let me out of here!
I'll return everything I stole!

410
00:26:15.390 --> 00:26:16.900
Mr. Haredas!

411
00:26:16.900 --> 00:26:18.490
Call Mr. Haredas over here!

412
00:26:18.490 --> 00:26:20.040
Will you please?!

413
00:26:21.600 --> 00:26:25.940
We won't let you out!
There's no telling what you'll do!

414
00:26:25.940 --> 00:26:29.230
How should we punish this young girl?!

415
00:26:29.230 --> 00:26:32.490
Do we flood her cage
or strike it with lightning?

416
00:26:32.490 --> 00:26:34.370
Damn cat burglar!

417
00:26:35.900 --> 00:26:38.680
I won't do anything...

418
00:26:38.680 --> 00:26:41.090
Just let me out already!

419
00:26:41.090 --> 00:26:42.940
No way!

420
00:26:44.100 --> 00:26:46.440
Hey, hey! Hey, hey!

421
00:26:46.440 --> 00:26:47.800
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

422
00:26:47.800 --> 00:26:49.520
Oh, Mr. Haredas!

423
00:26:49.520 --> 00:26:51.990
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

424
00:26:51.990 --> 00:26:54.130
Hey, hey! Hey, hey!

425
00:26:54.710 --> 00:26:56.290
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

426
00:26:56.290 --> 00:26:57.360
Hey!

427
00:26:57.360 --> 00:26:59.910
Hey, hey, young lady!

428
00:26:59.910 --> 00:27:01.100
Okay, stop that.

429
00:27:01.100 --> 00:27:04.970
I heard you were running amok again.

430
00:27:06.040 --> 00:27:07.270
Ta-da!

431
00:27:07.270 --> 00:27:10.710
But here I have just
the thing! Now, take a look!

432
00:27:10.710 --> 00:27:13.540
Tied tightly here are "wind knots"!

433
00:27:17.720 --> 00:27:20.100
– Mr. Haredas!
– Mr. Haredas!

434
00:27:23.000 --> 00:27:27.630
I'm in a real hurry here, so either
give me a hand or get my fist!

435
00:27:27.630 --> 00:27:29.100
– Mr. Haredas!
– Mr. Haredas!

436
00:27:29.100 --> 00:27:31.860
– Say something, Mr. Haredas!
– Say something, Mr. Haredas!

437
00:27:33.100 --> 00:27:36.500
Hey... Haredas... here...

438
00:27:37.120 --> 00:27:40.410
A surprise attack! She's a demon!

439
00:27:40.410 --> 00:27:42.710
The doctor! Someone call the doctor!

440
00:27:47.300 --> 00:27:49.000
She did what?

441
00:27:49.000 --> 00:27:53.920
She stole weather balls from the weather patch,
and she took our research notes?

442
00:27:53.920 --> 00:27:56.650
It is as you see, Mr. Haredas.

443
00:27:57.500 --> 00:27:58.690
Young lady...

444
00:27:59.500 --> 00:28:03.300
I used to be a thief, and now I'm a pirate.

445
00:28:04.690 --> 00:28:06.460
What's wrong with stealing?

446
00:28:06.460 --> 00:28:08.340
– She's pure evil!
– She's pure evil!

447
00:28:08.340 --> 00:28:10.800
– H-How can she even call herself human?!
– H-How can she even call herself human?!

448
00:28:10.800 --> 00:28:13.640
– We have a true villainess in our country!
– We have a true villainess in our country!

449
00:28:14.750 --> 00:28:16.840
Like I said...

450
00:28:16.840 --> 00:28:19.780
I'm trying to get out of this country!

451
00:28:19.780 --> 00:28:22.950
I'm begging you, just let me go already!

452
00:28:22.950 --> 00:28:26.740
I have to hurry! I gave back
everything I stole, didn't I?

453
00:28:26.740 --> 00:28:28.590
Come on, let me out!

454
00:28:28.590 --> 00:28:32.320
Stay back! She's a sinister one, all right!

455
00:28:35.810 --> 00:28:38.160
What's gotten into you all of a sudden?

456
00:28:38.900 --> 00:28:43.650
I heard you tried to steal a balloon
to go down to the surface.

457
00:28:43.650 --> 00:28:47.550
Amateurs can't use those.
You could have died!

458
00:28:49.840 --> 00:28:52.510
Look at the newspaper.

459
00:28:52.510 --> 00:28:54.710
The newspaper?

460
00:28:55.750 --> 00:28:58.910
There's coverage on a man named Luffy...

461
00:28:58.910 --> 00:29:00.450
He's my captain.

462
00:29:00.450 --> 00:29:01.770
What?

463
00:29:02.890 --> 00:29:04.820
Oh? This kid?

464
00:29:04.820 --> 00:29:09.140
He's the one who wreaked so much havoc
in the war that just happened.

465
00:29:09.140 --> 00:29:11.430
The infamous straw-hat rookie.

466
00:29:11.430 --> 00:29:15.190
While his crew was scattered
across the world...

467
00:29:15.190 --> 00:29:19.960
Luffy was left to fight
a difficult battle all on his own.

468
00:29:22.910 --> 00:29:27.780
In order to save Ace, he rushed
headlong into that Summit War...

469
00:29:33.650 --> 00:29:36.900
but Ace died right before his eyes!

470
00:29:36.900 --> 00:29:38.730
And I was just...

471
00:29:38.730 --> 00:29:40.520
oblivious to it!

472
00:29:42.200 --> 00:29:47.560
Luffy will definitely go
to our rendezvous point.

473
00:29:49.370 --> 00:29:52.540
Before he's completely broken...

474
00:29:55.400 --> 00:29:59.150
I need to go and be there for him!

475
00:30:04.350 --> 00:30:07.690
Oh! Hey, hey, hey! Young lady!

476
00:30:07.690 --> 00:30:09.580
Hurry and let her out!

477
00:30:09.580 --> 00:30:12.690
We locked up a young girl and made her cry!

478
00:30:12.690 --> 00:30:14.730
How could we be so cruel?!

479
00:30:14.730 --> 00:30:16.190
Mr. Haredas! The key!

480
00:30:16.190 --> 00:30:17.590
Right, the key!

481
00:30:17.590 --> 00:30:19.600
There. Now come on out.

482
00:30:19.600 --> 00:30:21.070
We're so sorry, young la–

483
00:30:27.340 --> 00:30:28.900
Where did she go?

484
00:30:28.900 --> 00:30:30.610
Mr. Haredas is gone too.

485
00:30:37.210 --> 00:30:39.750
– What?! How'd she get over there?!
– What?! How'd she get over there?!

486
00:30:41.520 --> 00:30:43.120
Thanks!

487
00:30:43.120 --> 00:30:44.220
So long!

488
00:30:44.220 --> 00:30:46.640
– Huh?! What the...?!
– Huh?! What the...?!

489
00:30:46.640 --> 00:30:49.740
She faked her tears
and took Mr. Haredas hostage!

490
00:30:49.740 --> 00:30:52.400
And she has the stolen goods again!

491
00:30:52.400 --> 00:30:56.570
Weatheria's weather science needs
to remain hidden from the world!

492
00:30:56.570 --> 00:30:58.290
After her!

493
00:30:58.290 --> 00:31:01.950
Anywhere will do! Just please,
take me down to the surface!

494
00:31:01.950 --> 00:31:03.040
Not possible...

495
00:31:03.040 --> 00:31:04.710
Make it possible!

496
00:31:06.100 --> 00:31:08.900
Luffy... You're safe, right?

497
00:31:08.900 --> 00:31:13.340
I'm sorry! You were always
the one to support us!

498
00:31:13.340 --> 00:31:16.950
Now that you need us, it's our turn to...!

499
00:31:16.950 --> 00:31:20.060
After her! Don't let her get away!

500
00:31:21.790 --> 00:31:26.400
Oh? Young lady, you don't
have to keep up the crying act.

501
00:31:27.630 --> 00:31:28.970
Stow it!

502
00:31:33.200 --> 00:31:36.910
Meanwhile, in the land where
the genius Vegapunk was born...

503
00:31:36.910 --> 00:31:40.010
Baldimore, a winter island country
known as Futureland...

504
00:31:43.080 --> 00:31:45.280
Intruder alert!

505
00:31:45.280 --> 00:31:48.790
Doctor Vegapunk's lab has been
breached! It's an intruder!

506
00:31:50.250 --> 00:31:52.590
Do not discharge firearms in the lab!

507
00:31:52.590 --> 00:31:55.960
Treat every single object
in there like a world treasure!

508
00:31:55.960 --> 00:31:56.990
Understood?!

509
00:31:56.990 --> 00:31:58.560
Roger that!

510
00:32:00.030 --> 00:32:01.700
Halt!

511
00:32:01.700 --> 00:32:04.500
Dammit! The Marines are here too?

512
00:32:08.270 --> 00:32:10.240
Nope, that'd be bad.

513
00:32:11.280 --> 00:32:12.640
Can't shoot in here!

514
00:32:13.680 --> 00:32:17.180
Treasure? That laboratory?

515
00:32:17.180 --> 00:32:18.180
Indeed.

516
00:32:18.180 --> 00:32:23.350
Vegapunk is now the lead scientist
for the entirety of the Marines.

517
00:32:23.350 --> 00:32:25.490
He is the pride of our country.

518
00:32:25.490 --> 00:32:29.290
One could even consider his brain
as one of mankind's greatest assets.

519
00:32:29.960 --> 00:32:34.160
This is where Vegapunk spent
the days of his youth.

520
00:32:36.830 --> 00:32:38.470
Take a look at that mountain.

521
00:32:38.470 --> 00:32:39.170
Huh?

522
00:32:39.170 --> 00:32:41.040
It has an odd shape, right?

523
00:32:41.040 --> 00:32:45.110
Yeah, now that you mention it,
what is that thing?

524
00:32:45.110 --> 00:32:47.540
He built that in his childhood,

525
00:32:47.540 --> 00:32:51.520
thinking about the citizens
who must endure this intense cold.

526
00:32:51.520 --> 00:32:57.350
He modified the forest animals so they
would assist in this arduous labor of love,

527
00:32:57.350 --> 00:32:58.760
but it remains incomplete.

528
00:32:59.820 --> 00:33:03.360
Something to warm the entire island:
a ground-heating system.

529
00:33:05.330 --> 00:33:06.530
However...

530
00:33:06.530 --> 00:33:09.330
there was a problem that plagued him...

531
00:33:09.330 --> 00:33:14.240
The ideas in his head
never saw the light of day.

532
00:33:14.240 --> 00:33:18.840
He lacked the resources and funding
to make them a reality.

533
00:33:18.840 --> 00:33:22.610
Just the sight of him crying
when he was unable to help us...

534
00:33:23.350 --> 00:33:27.380
was enough to warm our hearts.

535
00:33:30.890 --> 00:33:34.990
That's a super tearjerker of a story!

536
00:33:34.990 --> 00:33:36.230
You think so?

537
00:33:36.230 --> 00:33:40.860
We are all anxiously awaiting
the day he comes home.

538
00:33:42.800 --> 00:33:48.410
Now that you know, I ask that you never
return to that laboratory, what with its...

539
00:33:48.410 --> 00:33:49.670
self-destruct button.

540
00:33:49.670 --> 00:33:50.870
The hell...?!

541
00:33:50.870 --> 00:33:55.710
That's the worst switch anyone could install,
and you just casually mention it?!

542
00:33:56.980 --> 00:33:59.280
I didn't know about that switch...

543
00:33:59.280 --> 00:34:04.090
Hey, old guy, let's just go home
and have some warm tea!

544
00:34:04.090 --> 00:34:05.920
No can do!

545
00:34:05.920 --> 00:34:09.390
The ice-breaker ship is my
only way off this island,

546
00:34:09.390 --> 00:34:11.960
and it's in that laboratory, right?

547
00:34:13.700 --> 00:34:16.630
I have things I need to do.

548
00:34:16.630 --> 00:34:21.100
You see, I just read in the news
that my captain's not doing so hot.

549
00:34:22.270 --> 00:34:23.110
See ya!

550
00:34:23.110 --> 00:34:25.110
I owe you big time!

551
00:34:25.910 --> 00:34:30.010
Wait! Whatever you do,
do not push the self destruct button!

552
00:34:30.010 --> 00:34:32.120
Like I would, you codger!

553
00:34:32.120 --> 00:34:34.520
Why'd he install that anyway?!

554
00:34:36.590 --> 00:34:40.090
Hot damn, this is super impressive.

555
00:34:40.090 --> 00:34:43.290
These are all just inventions
he thought up as a kid?

556
00:34:43.290 --> 00:34:47.030
A lot of these ideas are a couple
hundred years ahead of their time.

557
00:34:48.270 --> 00:34:52.900
They're right. As an engineer, I would
hate it if anything happened to this place.

558
00:34:52.900 --> 00:34:56.240
Hey, did you hear? Apparently,
there's an intruder in the lab!

559
00:34:56.240 --> 00:34:58.710
No way! That's terrible news!

560
00:34:58.710 --> 00:35:03.650
Word is, each and every blueprint
in there is a priceless treasure.

561
00:35:03.650 --> 00:35:08.290
Take precautions, men! If anything
in the genius Vegapunk's lab gets damaged,

562
00:35:08.290 --> 00:35:10.290
it is a severe criminal offense!

563
00:35:10.290 --> 00:35:11.190
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

564
00:35:13.560 --> 00:35:15.360
Oh, a pirate mark!

565
00:35:36.480 --> 00:35:38.550
Lemme ask just one thing.

566
00:35:38.550 --> 00:35:42.120
If, by some freak chance,
I were to press that switch...

567
00:35:43.120 --> 00:35:44.220
Old guy?

568
00:35:45.090 --> 00:35:47.490
Would it be my fault?

569
00:35:47.490 --> 00:35:49.360
– Obviously!
– Obviously!

570
00:35:50.260 --> 00:35:53.900
This incident in Futureland
is forever referred to as:

571
00:35:53.900 --> 00:35:56.670
"The Nightmare of Baldimore."

572
00:36:02.510 --> 00:36:06.140
Thank you so much, Dark Lord Satan!

573
00:36:07.580 --> 00:36:14.520
I never thought I'd see the day when these
guys were finally captured and behind bars!

574
00:36:14.520 --> 00:36:19.490
I can't explain it, but when you played
that song you composed for us...

575
00:36:19.490 --> 00:36:22.390
...courage and fighting spirit welled up inside us!

576
00:36:22.390 --> 00:36:25.830
For the first time in our lives,
we stood our ground!

577
00:36:26.900 --> 00:36:29.700
Of course, we lost anyway,

578
00:36:29.700 --> 00:36:32.970
so you were the one who defeated them.

579
00:36:32.970 --> 00:36:37.910
But thanks to your actions,
our kidnapped villagers are safe once more.

580
00:36:39.340 --> 00:36:42.750
Oh, you! Don't thank me,
I only helped a little.

581
00:36:43.480 --> 00:36:47.680
Neither gods nor devils
are spurred to action by inaction.

582
00:36:47.680 --> 00:36:49.320
These are dark times.

583
00:36:49.320 --> 00:36:51.690
My intervention was merely an attempt

584
00:36:51.690 --> 00:36:55.660
to ensure you carry the will
to stand against future misdeeds.

585
00:36:55.660 --> 00:36:57.390
How benevolent!

586
00:36:57.390 --> 00:37:01.000
I feel like we can really make the change!

587
00:37:01.000 --> 00:37:04.100
Thank you very much, Lord Satan!

588
00:37:04.900 --> 00:37:07.740
And with that, my debt is settled.

589
00:37:07.740 --> 00:37:12.110
At any rate, I could barely
believe that news article.

590
00:37:12.110 --> 00:37:15.110
I hope you are well, Luffy.

591
00:37:15.110 --> 00:37:17.910
My heart shares your pain.

592
00:37:17.910 --> 00:37:20.250
Though... I do not have a heart.

593
00:37:20.250 --> 00:37:23.450
Luffy, let us sing together!

594
00:37:23.450 --> 00:37:26.720
Without further ado, let me soothe your heart!

595
00:37:26.720 --> 00:37:30.390
Dammit! They had an
actual devil as a bodyguard!

596
00:37:30.390 --> 00:37:35.730
If only we had gotten these single-elbowed
freak shows back to our homeland,

597
00:37:35.730 --> 00:37:39.240
we could have made a killing
with them on display!

598
00:37:39.240 --> 00:37:41.140
Now, then...

599
00:37:41.140 --> 00:37:44.570
If we put these two-elbowed,
long-armed freak shows on display,

600
00:37:44.570 --> 00:37:48.080
we could make a killing off of that!

601
00:37:48.080 --> 00:37:50.510
P-Please wait just a minute.

602
00:37:50.510 --> 00:37:55.090
If you do that, you will be
no better than them!

603
00:37:55.090 --> 00:37:56.590
– Huh?
– Huh?

604
00:37:56.590 --> 00:37:58.720
Everybody, listen!

605
00:37:59.790 --> 00:38:04.630
What?! Let them go?!
If we do that, they'll just–

606
00:38:04.630 --> 00:38:09.330
It will be okay. They, too,
have made a deal with the devil!

607
00:38:10.930 --> 00:38:13.570
Heed my words, you three.

608
00:38:13.570 --> 00:38:19.440
For if you break your contract with me
by troubling this nation once more,

609
00:38:19.440 --> 00:38:22.280
I will...

610
00:38:22.280 --> 00:38:24.450
eat your hearts!

611
00:38:26.420 --> 00:38:29.420
We are humbled by your mercy!

612
00:38:29.420 --> 00:38:31.520
We'll return home immediately!

613
00:38:31.520 --> 00:38:35.230
We'll never come near this country again!

614
00:38:38.160 --> 00:38:39.430
– And up we go!
– And up we go!

615
00:38:39.430 --> 00:38:41.130
Huh? What?!

616
00:38:41.130 --> 00:38:44.000
Why?! What do you think you're doing?!

617
00:38:44.000 --> 00:38:46.040
– And off we go!
– And off we go!

618
00:38:46.040 --> 00:38:48.740
Devils aren't real, you bonehead!

619
00:38:48.740 --> 00:38:52.540
You're pretty strong, but you're
helpless once we tie you up!

620
00:38:52.540 --> 00:38:55.950
When we bring back this
rare, moving skeleton...

621
00:38:55.950 --> 00:38:58.110
...we'll be trillionaires!

622
00:38:58.110 --> 00:39:02.320
Wait a second! I have somewhere
I really need to get back to!

623
00:39:02.320 --> 00:39:04.390
Lord Satan!

624
00:39:04.390 --> 00:39:08.460
This is a disaster!
They abducted our Lord Satan!

625
00:39:08.460 --> 00:39:09.690
Everyone,

626
00:39:09.690 --> 00:39:12.730
prepare to summon a new devil!

627
00:39:12.730 --> 00:39:17.130
That's right! We're still able
to summon devils with our underwear!

628
00:39:19.770 --> 00:39:23.010
Luffy. We should sing together
when things are tough.

629
00:39:23.010 --> 00:39:25.540
As a musician, I live for those moments.

630
00:39:25.540 --> 00:39:27.050
So please wait for me!

631
00:39:27.050 --> 00:39:30.250
I promise... I promise I will be there!

632
00:39:30.250 --> 00:39:31.380
Luffy...

633
00:39:32.020 --> 00:39:33.250
Luffy...!

634
00:39:33.250 --> 00:39:34.520
Before that...

635
00:39:34.520 --> 00:39:36.890
Help me!
